						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Naḷa (1497 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Registers grant of some lands as the gift of <hi rend="bold">Chikka Narasā-Nāyaka,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Narasā-Nāyaka,</hi> towards garlands and food offerings for the god. The measure <hi rend="italic">Rājavibhāṭaṉ</hi> is mentioned. The grant was made on the occasion of a lunar eclipse. The details of the date viz., <hi rend="bold">Naḷa, Makara, śu. Paurṇamī, Wednesday, Āyilyam</hi> correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1497, January 18, ·72, f.d.n. ·25.</hi> (lunar eclipse).</p>						

						</summary>
